QUADRATIC DISCRIMINANT ANALYSIS (QDA)
1. Introduction
Quadratic Discriminant Analysis (QDA) is a supervised machine learning algorithm used mainly for classification problems. It is an extension of Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA), but unlike LDA, QDA does not assume that all classes have the same covariance matrix. Instead, each class has its own covariance matrix, allowing the algorithm to create quadratic (curved) decision boundaries rather than straight lines. This makes QDA suitable for datasets where the relationship between features and classes is nonlinear.

