2.1 Binary QDA
Definition
Binary Quadratic Discriminant Analysis is used when the dataset contains only two classes. It calculates separate covariance matrices for each class and creates a quadratic decision boundary to classify new observations. Binary QDA is useful when the two classes cannot be separated by a straight line.
Flowchart

