                     │
                     ▼
        Predict the New Class
                     │
                     ▼
          Final Prediction
Examples
	• Fraud or Not Fraud 
	• Disease Positive or Negative 
	• Loan Approved or Rejected 
	• Spam or Not Spam 

2.2 Multi-class QDA
Definition
Multi-class Quadratic Discriminant Analysis is used when there are more than two classes. The algorithm estimates a separate covariance matrix for each class and computes multiple quadratic decision boundaries. It assigns a new observation to the class with the highest probability.
